20/05/2011
OSLO, Norway -- The country has decided to suspend financial aid to debt-ridden Greece as Athens failed to meet its obligations to receive the funds, the foreign ministry announced on Thursday (May 19th). 
Norway is not a member of the EU but is part of the European Economic Area that encompasses the 27 EU members, Iceland and Liechtenstein. 
Norway's 30m-euro grant was intended for environmental and health projects. 
(Capital.gr, SKAI, Sitel, MIA - 19/05/11)
